<section class="fdb-block pb-sm-1 pt-sm-1 pb-md-5 pt-md-5" data-block-type="contents" data-id="1" draggable="true" id="thelions">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 ml-md-auto pt-5 text-center">
        <h2>Increasingly fragmented lion populations</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1rem;" class="mt-4">Over the last 20 years, the African lion has lost approximately 42% of its habitat leaving the population increasingly fragmented.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 1rem;" class="">Understanding lion movements between areas is critical for conservation decision-making and maintaining genetic diversity. Therefore, it is imperative that researchers and conservationists collaborate on a broader scale to exchange knowledge with the aim to improve connectivity and the sustainability of lion populations across their remaining range. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 mb-4 mb-md-0">
        <img alt="image" class="img-fluid ml-lg-4 mr-lg-auto" id="historic-range-img" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lynn-de-souza/image/upload/v1548347053/LINC%20website/About/RangeMap.png">
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row align-items-center mt-1 mb-2">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 mb-4 mb-md-0">
        <img alt="image" class="img-fluid" src="
      https://res.cloudinary.com/lynn-de-souza/image/upload/v1548347049/LINC%20website/About/lincMapFront.png">
      </div>
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6 ml-md-auto text-center pl-lg-5">
        <p>LINC is a technological solution that generates a rich source of information on lions across their range. These data enable researchers, conservationists and decision-makers to pinpoint priority areas where connection is known to be occurring. The system employs cutting-edge methodologies for sharing data across research initiatives and includes innovative features such as automated lion recognition tools. </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

