      <div class="col-12 col-lg-7 col-md-8 mr-auto px-5 pt-5 pt-md-0">
        <h2>First-of-its kind recognition algorithm</h2>
        <p>The computer vision (CV) system detects lion faces based on a Haar classifier. These are then processed using a Convolutional Neural Network that develops classifiers for each individual lion.
        <br>
        <br>
        The facial recognition software currently uses a combination of OpenCV and the Caffe deep learning framework to develop the classifiers it is currently running on a CUDA based NVIDA GPU. LINC is an <%= link_to 'open source', "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software", target: "_blank"  %> software to support collaboration where developers and citizen scientists around the world can work together to improve and scale up the artificial intelligence aspects of the system.</p>
      </div>
